ğŸ“° News Summarization & Sentiment Analysis
ğŸ“Œ Overview
This project is a News Summarization & Sentiment Analysis tool built using Flask, Streamlit, and NLTK. It fetches the latest news articles for a given company, summarizes them, analyzes the sentiment, and provides a comparative sentiment distribution. It also supports Text-to-Speech (TTS) functionality in Hindi.

ğŸš€ Features
1.Fetch Latest News: Scrapes Bing News for articles related to a given company.
2.Summarization: Uses sumy library to generate a concise summary.
3.Sentiment Analysis: Uses nltk's SentimentIntensityAnalyzer to classify news as Positive, Negative, or Neutral.
4.Comparative Sentiment Analysis: Aggregates sentiment scores across multiple articles.
5.Text-to-Speech (TTS): Converts summaries into Hindi audio.
6.Streamlit UI: Provides an interactive web app for users.

ğŸ› ï¸ Tech Stack
1.Frontend: Streamlit
2.Backend: Flask (REST API)
3.Web Scraping: BeautifulSoup
4.Summarization: sumy (LSA Summarizer)
5.Sentiment Analysis: NLTK (VADER)
6.Text-to-Speech: gTTS

ğŸ¯ Future Enhancements
1.Improve summarization techniques (BERT, GPT models)
2.Add more news sources (Google News, Yahoo Finance)
3.Enhance UI with interactive graphs (Plotly, Altair)
